Actually, this method should work. I made the same feature in my project. But after comparing our approach I see a few differences. Instead `alarmManager.setExact` use `alarmManager.setRepeating` as you need this Push to repeat. **Also, there is no guarantee that Push will be sent exactly in a specific second.** It could be later. Just wait some time. Here is my working example for sending Push every weekend. Maybe you find something useful for you.


    private void initLocalPushNotificationBroadcast() {
        AlarmManager alarmManager = (AlarmManager) getSystemService(ALARM_SERVICE);
        Intent intent = new Intent(this, AlarmReceiver.class);
        PendingIntent broadcast = PendingIntent.getBroadcast(this, 11100, intent, PendingIntent.FLAG_UPDATE_CURRENT | PendingIntent.FLAG_IMMUTABLE);
        long time = Utils.getStartCurrentWeekInMilliseconds(1) - Utils.MILLISECONDS_IN_15_HOUR;
        alarmManager.setRepeating(
                AlarmManager.RTC_WAKEUP,
                time,
                AlarmManager.INTERVAL_DAY * 7,
                broadcast);
    }


    public static long getStartCurrentWeekInMilliseconds(int offsetFromCurrentWeek) {
        Calendar cal = Calendar.getInstance();
        cal.setTimeZone(TIME_ZONE);
        cal.set(Calendar.HOUR_OF_DAY, 0);
        cal.clear(Calendar.MINUTE);
        cal.clear(Calendar.SECOND);
        cal.clear(Calendar.MILLISECOND);
        // get start of this week in milliseconds
        cal.set(Calendar.DAY_OF_WEEK, Calendar.MONDAY);
        // start of the week
        cal.add(Calendar.WEEK_OF_YEAR, offsetFromCurrentWeek);
        return cal.getTimeInMillis();
    }

Call `initLocalPushNotificationBroadcast` in `onCreate` method in Application class.

And here is AlarmReceiver:

    class AlarmReceiver : BroadcastReceiver() {

    override fun onReceive(context: Context, intent: Intent?) {

        val resultIntent = Intent(context, RankingActivity::class.java)
        resultIntent.putExtra(WEEKLY_PERFORMANCE_EVENT, true)
        resultIntent.putExtra(MainActivity.PN_RECEIVED_DATE, System.currentTimeMillis())
